{{italic title}}

'''''Van Nostrand's Scientific Encyclopedia''''' is an [[encyclopedia]] published in the [[United States]]. Currently in a three volume 10th [[Edition (book)|edition]], it was published in two volumes for editions 6 to 9. The 8th edition is available as two [[CD-ROM|CD ROMs]].

The first edition was published in 1938 by the  D. Van Nostrand Company, Inc.<ref>[https://lccn.loc.gov/38008703 ''Van Nostrand's scientific encyclopedia; aeronautics, astronomy, botany, chemistry, engineering, geology, mathematics, medicine, mineralogy, navigation, physics, zoology'', New York: D. Van Nostrand company, Inc. c. 1938], loc.gov. Retrieved 28 May 2018.</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last1 = L. | first1 = H. R. | title = Van Nostrand's Scientific Encyclopedia | journal = Nature | volume = 142 | pages = 853–854 | year = 1938 | doi = 10.1038/142853a0|bibcode = 1938Natur.142..853H | issue=3602| pmc = 199381 }}</ref> From about 1976 the encyclopedia was published by the Van Nostrand Reinhold Company. From the late 1990s it was published by [[John Wiley and Sons]] and by Wiley-Interscience.

More than 4,000 pages long, the work provides a thorough [[Science|scientific]] reference, while establishing a midpoint between massive multi-volume science encyclopedias and handheld [[Reference work|reference books]].

This work is sometimes compared to the ''[[McGraw-Hill Concise Encyclopedia of Science & Technology]]''.

